ontainers-managed Docker containers during tests. It supplies the @Testcontainers and @Container annotations so containers can be started and stopped per test method or shared across a test class.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/org.testcontainers/junit-jupiter/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:1441:| `org.testcontainers:testcontainers` | [1.17.6<br>- 2.0.5](metadata/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Testcontainers is a Java library for JUnit tests that provides lightweight, throwaway Docker containers for databases, web browsers, and other services. It helps integration tests run against real dependencies instead of mocks or in-memory substitutes.</details> | [4.3% (43/1,008 calls)](stats/org.testcontainers/testcontainers/) |\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:221:If your tests use Docker (either with explicit Docker process invocation or through some library method call), all images have to be declared in `required-docker-images` file.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:224:Only Docker images that are listed in the [`allowed-docker-images` directory](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images) can be used for testing.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:226:That pull request should add a new file in the [`allowed-docker-images` directory](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images)\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:227:with the name in the format `Dockerfile-<dockerImageName>` (replace all occurrence of `/` with `_`) .\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:236:   * If your test uses Docker image, and you didn't specify it in the `required-docker-images.txt` file, the test will fail.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:237:   * If your test uses Docker image that is not listed in [allowed docker images list](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/AllowedDockerImages.txt),\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:239:   * Only docker images that are in both `required-docker-images.txt` and in the `allowed docker images list`\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:243:See an [example](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-mysql_mysql-server).\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:311:# Maven Central and Docker registry failures have no such boundary (Gradle owns\n./docs/tests.md:16:  Docker images it needs in `required-docker-images.txt`, and is the unit the\n./docs/tests.md:59:  declared, pre-pulled `allowed-docker-image` with networking disabled, and\n./docs/e2e.md:17:`pullAllowedDockerImages` for the resolved coordinate, then runs the full infra\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:40:     - allowed Docker image entries or test resources only when the native test requires them\n./docs/functional-spec.md:68:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every Monday, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:125:| `docker` | PR | PR updates allowed Docker images used by tests. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:232:- **Declared Docker images.** Tests that use Docker must declare every image they need in `required-docker-images.txt`. Each image must already appear in `tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/allowed-docker-images/Dockerfile-<dockerImageName>`. Tests fail otherwise.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:240:- **Docker isolation.** Docker images used in tests are pre-pulled from `allowed-docker-images`, after which the runner disables Docker networking for deterministic, isolated test runs.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:244:- **Docker tag sync.** Dependabot updates to `allowed-docker-images` trigger `sync-docker-tags.yml`, which back-commits the synchronized tags into the Dependabot PR.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:259:- **Determinism.** Tests must be reproducible. Network-dependent tests are not allowed except where they declare an `allowed-docker-image` and run against that pre-pulled image with networking disabled.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:332:`./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages checkMetadataFiles test -Pcoordinates=<group:artifact:version>`.\n./docs/tck.md:98:## 6. Docker image management\n./docs/tck.md:102:| `pullAllowedDockerImages` | Pre-pull only the images a coordinate's metadata allows, before networking is disabled for isolated runs (§FS-repository-functional-spec.5.3). |\n./docs/tck.md:103:| `checkAllowedDockerImages` | Scan allowed images for vulnerabilities with grype, either all images or only those changed between two commits (§CI-scan-docker-images). |\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/contributing/questions.json:20:    \"help\": \"Enter the docker images (press enter after each image name you enter) that you want to use in your tests. Docker image declaration consists of two parts separated with \\\":\\\" in the following format: \\\"imageName:version\\\". When you finish adding docker images, type \\\"-\\\" to terminate the inclusion process.\"\n./AGENTS.md:5:- Docker\n./AGENTS.md:29:- Pre-fetch Docker images allowed by metadata (used in tests) for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n./AGENTS.md:44:  - ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\n./AGENTS.md:48:  - ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=1/64\n./AGENTS.md:65:## Docker Image Vulnerability Scanning\n./AGENTS.md:67:  - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages --baseCommit=$(git rev-parse origin/master) --newCommit=$(git rev-parse HEAD)\n./AGENTS.md:69:  - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages\n./forge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py:44:LIBRARY_PREFLIGHT_DETERMINISTIC_KINDS = (\"dependency\", \"docker_ima